did.head: Descriptive Summary

langmaterial.language: The language of the materials is English

did.abstract: The Annual Report Collection consists of reports submitted to the Office of the President from each department of the university in the spring semester.

custodhist.head: Provenance
custodhist.p: The original annual report material was sent to the University Archives from the office of President David G. Carter on July 27, 2001. It included reports from 1991-1992 through 1996-1997.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: The Annual Report Collection consists of reports submitted to the Office of the President from each department of the university in the spring semester. The first group of reports sent to the University Archives for preservation dated from 1991-1997. Earlier annual reports dating from 1973-1990 were collected from various sources and later added to the collection. Current and past reports are added as they become available. The reports appear in the order in which they were received unless otherwise indicated. Access to faculty resumes or other personalized information included in the reports is restricted.
Series I - 1973-1979; This series includes the earliest annual reports available. These include reports from the Office of Research and the School of Arts and Sciences.

Series II - 1983-1984; 1987-1989; This series includes one Special Services report for 1983-1984, 26 reports from 1987-1988 (Academic Affairs to Student Affairs) and 8 reports from 1988-1989 (Academic Affairs).
Series II - 1990-1995; This series includes annual reports submitted to the archives from the Office of the President for the 1990-91 academic year through the 1994-95 academic year.
Series III - 1995-1999; This series includes annual reports from the 1995-1996 academic year through the 1999-2000 academic year.
Series IV - 2000-2004; This series includes annual reports from the 2000-2001 academic year through 2004-2005 academic year.
Series V - 2005-2009; This series includes annual reports from the 2005-2006 through 2009-2010.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The reports were placed in acid-free folders and divided into series chronologically by academic year. Material is in the order in which it was received unless otherwise noted.
The files are grouped into 5 series:

relatedmaterial.head: Related Material
relatedmaterial.p: A collection of Annual Reports submitted to other President’s of the Connecticut University System in the late 1960’s can be found in the Office of the President - Searle F. Charles. The University Archives has a substantial collection of university archives material and also houses the Connecticut Studies Collection. For more detailed information on these collections please contact the staff member at the reference desk.
